p: In thrombolytic docking assay, 4-terpineol (−5.254 kcal/mol), α-cadinene (−5.720 kcal/mol), spatulenol (−6.190 kcal/mol) and T-cadinol (−6.300 kcal/mol) showed better biding affinity than streptokinase (−5.102 kcal/mol) against tissue plasminogen activator receptor ( Table 3). Among them T-cadinol exhibited the best result by interacting with two hydrogen bonds (SER195 and GLN192) and one hydrophobic bond (CYS220) ( Figure 7).
